bright colours and stuff and all the bright stickers and the pens

00:00:50.680 --> 00:00:57.920
and it really grabs your attention and it makes you
more intrigued in what the campaign’s about.

00:00:58.160 --> 00:01:04.680
-We created a series of characters
which look cartoonish, look like a comic.

00:01:04.760 --> 00:01:10.520
But the truth is that each character represents something beyond. 

00:01:10.520 --> 00:01:17.720
So, we’re talking about this represents Mass Media. 
This represents Tobacco Industry, Marketing, Product Placement.

00:01:17.720 --> 00:01:23.840
We show how these lot work together to place
the cigarette, as a product, in media to promote it.

00:01:23.880 --> 00:01:27.560
I think it’s a good approach. I mean it will
definitely catch the younger people’s eyes

00:01:27.680 --> 00:01:33.920
because most people are into their comic book characters and
all that and that’s how it initially strikes them at first glance.

00:01:33.920 --> 00:01:41.360
It’s a good way to rope people in and you seem to have very valid points
so you seem to be able to engage people in a good conversation

00:01:41.360 --> 00:01:42.880
and get your point across.

00:01:43.240 --> 00:01:46.720
I actually thought it was quite appealing, 'cause when I
saw it I actually thought it was something from ‘Marvel’.

00:01:46.800 --> 00:01:52.320
Most people, when they see those campaigns against smoking,
they think “Aw nah, allow it,”

00:01:52.360 --> 00:01:57.600
They’ll come with a negative outlook, 'cause…
imagine someone smoking, they look at this

00:01:57.720 --> 00:02:01.560
and they won’t even know that it’s about smoking, they’ll come
and they listen to you and that. They’ll be like “…..”

00:02:01.760 --> 00:02:05.360
-[laughter]
